Commentary Text: Umran Malik to Arshdeep Singh, out Arshdeep Singh Run Out!! A comedy of errors. Malik fails to take the hat-trick, but that's the fourth wicket of the over. No runs conceded. Four wickets and a maiden! On a length around off and Arshdeep Singh slaps it to cover and sets up for a single. The throw comes in at the keeper's end and Arshdeep's run-out, Rabada sends him back, but he has no chance to get back in. Arshdeep Singh run out (J Suchith/Pooran) 0(1)

Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Shahrukh Khan, no run, Shahrukh Khan has been given out - caught at point. And he has decided to challenge the call. Was there some bat involved, or did it come off the helmet? Nothing on UltraEdge, there's a flat line. And the onfield decision has to be overturned. Was a short and quick ball by Natarajan and Shahrukh Khan got beaten on his pull. Struck on the helmet and the ball flies straight to the fielder at point. Nasty blow that as the batter removes his helmet and checks if he is fine. All done and we are ready to roll

Commentary Text: Umran Malik to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught&Bowled!! This is spectacular, Jitesh has been bounced out by Umran - banged in short and just outside off, Jitesh was swivelling across on the pull, but the pace is just too good for him, gets a top-edge that lobs back in the path of the bowler. Umran runs forward and then completes a two-handed catch, right in front of the batter and he's off on a celebratory run. The field was changed after the previous ball and he was asked to drag the pull, such is Umran's pace that Jitesh was always taking a big risk in doing so. Jitesh Sharma c and b Umran Malik 11(8) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: J Suchith to Bairstow, out Lbw!! Long long shout for LBW, a pleading appeal and Bairstow has been given out LBW, he has a chat with his partner and wants a review. It's a fair delivery and Bairstow has been struck on the back-knee. This looks trouble for Bairstow, nothing on UltraEdge. Onto ball-tracking: Impact is in line and it's hitting the top of middle-stump, three reds and Bairstow is OUT. Nicely bowled by Suchith, drifted in and then got the ball to straighten on the right-hander, Bairstow shuffled across on the big sweep and missed, the only thing that could have saved him was the impact, but he's struck in front off, the rest being a mere formality. Bairstow lbw b J Suchith 12(10) [4s-2]

Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Pooran!! Shout for LBW, but the angle was possibly taking it outside the line of off-stump - Prabhsimran shuffled a long way across on the flick and missed. Pooran was interested, so was the bowler - KW takes a lot of time and signals for the DRS, they were actually appealing for a caught behind, hang on! UltraEdge has caught a thin inside edge onto the pads, and then has lobbed nicely through to the keeper. The review is successful and the original call has to be overturned, Prabhsimran is OUT and Punjab have lost both openers now. Prabhsimran c Pooran b T Natarajan 14(11) [4s-2]
